text: The movie has almost nothing in common with the 60s TV series.  But that's okay.  They just bought the title.  It's still an entertaining film, filled with just the right amount of humor to make the entire flick work.  It's not "campy."  The humor is subtle and evenly distributed.  Henry Cavill demonstrates that he has a penchant for sly humor, so this could provide him with an avenue of escape from simply being type-cast as Superman.  For his sake I hope so as he clearly has a wide range in his acting abilities.  Box office receipts weren't great, so I guess we won't be seeing anything more, which is too bad.  So many worse films get sequels.

text: A real travesty this underperformed in the box office, everything from directing to acting was top notch. This film was full of style, and the comedy was the best too, nothing like those stupid quip jokes in recent movies. A totally underated film. It might be the name and (lack of)marketing that stopped people from finding this gem.  I really hope this becomes a cult classic big enough that it might actually see some sequels, hopefully before Henry and Army are too old. Same goes for The Nice Guys, another film in the same position.
